Power lines and pylons in front of Eskom's Lethabo power station. eNCA JOHANNESBURG - Eskom will be implementing load reduction in areas of the Free State, Mpumalanga, Limpopo and KwaZulu-Natal. The load reduction will take place between 5pm and 9pm on Friday. READ: Eskom suspends load-shedding In Limpopo, customers in Mopani and Capricorn Districts will be affected. In the Free State, Lejweleputswa District and Thabo Mofutsanyana District will be experiencing load reduction. KwaZulu-Natal and Mpumalanga will also be experiencing power cuts. Eskom Load Reduction Notice
